  "title": "Driver and Care Assistant #SGUnitedJobs",
  "description": "<p><u>Driver</u></p>\n<p><strong>. </strong>Transport residents from the nursing home for their routine medical</p>\n<p>appointments<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Co-ordinate with the Manager in the planning of the route and time of transport.<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Maintain cleanliness and working condition of the van.<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Attends to any other delivery requirements or errands when needed.<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Primary education or equivalent<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Able to speak and understand simple English<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Good organisation ability<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Class 3 Driving</p>\n<p><strong>. </strong>Defensive Driving</p>\n<p><strong>. </strong>CPR + AED</p>\n<p><u>Clinical Care</u></p>\n<p><strong>. </strong>Assists the registered nurses in the delivery of nursing care to the residents in the Home.<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Assists the physiotherapist in the delivery of therapeutic activities to the residents in the Home<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Helps to maintain a clean, safe and neat environment for the residents in the nursing home.<br>\n<strong>. </strong>Accompanies residents to the hospital/polyclinic for follow-up appointments.</p>\n<p>Successful applicants without the qualifications will be sent for Certificate in Community Care (Community Care Traineeship Programme) with all courses funded by the employer.</p>",
